    <section>
      <title>Define Listeners</title>

      <para>Drools supports adding 3 types of listeners to KnowledgeSessions.
      The Drools-Spring module now supports all 3 of them (AgendaListener,
      WorkingMemoryListener, ProcessEventListener).</para>

      <section>
        <title>&lt;drools:eventListener&gt;'s parameters as
        attributes:</title>

        <table>
          <tgroup align="left" cols="3" colsep="1" rowsep="1">
            <thead>
              <row>
                <entry align="center">Attribute</entry>

                <entry align="center">Required</entry>

                <entry align="center">Description</entry>
              </row>
            </thead>

            <tbody>
              <row>
                <entry>ref</entry>

                <entry>No</entry>

                <entry>A reference to another declared bean. <para /><para>If
                a <emphasis>ref</emphasis> is not provided, it is expected
                that a nested bean is declared inside this
                <emphasis>eventListener</emphasis> tag.</para></entry>
              </row>

              <row>
                <entry>type</entry>

                <entry>No</entry>

                <entry><emphasis>agenda-event-listener</emphasis> or
                <emphasis>process-event-listener</emphasis> or
                <emphasis>working-memory-event-listener</emphasis></entry>
              </row>
            </tbody>
          </tgroup>
        </table>

        <example>
          <title>AgendaListener configuration example - using a
          bean:ref.</title>

          <programlisting language="xml">  &lt;drools:resource id="resource1" type="DRL" source="classpath:org/drools/container/spring/testSpring.drl"/&gt;

  &lt;drools:kbase id="kbase1"&gt;
    &lt;drools:resources&gt;
      &lt;drools:resource ref="resource1"/&gt;
    &lt;/drools:resources&gt;
  &lt;/drools:kbase&gt;

  &lt;bean id="mock-agenda-listener" class="org.drools.container.spring.MockAgendaEventListener" /&gt;

  &lt;drools:ksession id="statelessSession" type="stateless" name="stateless1" kbase="kbase1"&gt;
    &lt;drools:eventListener ref="mock-agenda-listener" type="agenda-event-listener"/&gt;
  &lt;/drools:ksession&gt;
</programlisting>
        </example>
      </section>

      <section>
        <title>&lt;drools:eventListener&gt;'s parameters as nested
        elements:</title>

        <itemizedlist>
          <listitem>
            <para>bean</para>

            <itemizedlist>
              <listitem>
                <para>class = String</para>
              </listitem>

              <listitem>
                <para>name = String</para>
              </listitem>
            </itemizedlist>
          </listitem>
        </itemizedlist>

        <example>
          <title>AgendaListener configuration example - using nested
          bean.</title>

          <programlisting language="xml">  &lt;drools:resource id="resource1" type="DRL" source="classpath:org/drools/container/spring/testSpring.drl"/&gt;

  &lt;drools:kbase id="kbase1"&gt;
    &lt;drools:resources&gt;
      &lt;drools:resource ref="resource1"/&gt;
    &lt;/drools:resources&gt;
  &lt;/drools:kbase&gt;

  &lt;drools:ksession id="statelessSession" type="stateless" name="stateless1" kbase="kbase1"&gt;

    &lt;drools:eventListener type="agenda-event-listener"&gt;
      &lt;bean class="org.drools.container.spring.MockAgendaEventListener"/&gt;
    &lt;/drools:eventListener&gt;

  &lt;/drools:ksession&gt;

</programlisting>
        </example>
      </section>

      <section>
        <title>&lt;drools:eventListener&gt;'s - Points to Note</title>

        <note>
          <para>Important Things to note while using the
          <emphasis>drools:eventListener</emphasis>.</para>

          <itemizedlist>
            <listitem>
              <para>ref</para>

              <itemizedlist>
                <listitem>
                  <para>Either the <emphasis>ref</emphasis> attribute or a
                  nested <emphasis>bean</emphasis> is mandatory!</para>
                </listitem>
              </itemizedlist>
            </listitem>

            <listitem>
              <para>type</para>

              <itemizedlist>
                <listitem>
                  <para>If the <emphasis>type</emphasis> is not specified,
                  then the bean is introspected at runtime and the exact
                  interface(s) inferred. For example: if the bean implements
                  <emphasis>org.drools.event.rule.AgendaEventListener</emphasis>
                  and
                  <emphasis>org.drools.event.process.MockProcessEventListener</emphasis>
                  interfaces, this bean is added as an agenda listener and
                  also as a process event listener.</para>
                </listitem>
              </itemizedlist>
            </listitem>
          </itemizedlist>
        </note>
      </section>
    </section>
